Steps to Execute a Batch Apex
Step 1: Open Developer Console
Go to Setup → Developer Console
Step 2: Open Execute Anonymous Window
Click: Debug → Open Execute Anonymous Window
Step 3: Write Execution Code
MyBatchClass batch = new MyBatchClass();
Id batchId = Database.executeBatch(batch, 200);
Step 4: Execute
Click "Execute" button
Step 5: Monitor the Job
Go to: Setup → Apex Jobs
Find your batch job by the Job ID
Check status and progress
Step 6: Verify Results
Check that records were processed correctly
Review any errors in the job details
